[[File:Finlandia 2017 logo.png|thumb|upright|Official exhibition logo]]
'''Finlandia 2017 European Stamp Exhibition''' was an international [[stamp exhibition]] held 24–28 May 2017 at the [[Tampere Hall]] in [[Tampere]], Finland. The exhibition was granted patronage from the [[Federation of European Philatelic Associations]] (FEPA) and the [[Fédération Internationale de Philatélie]] (FIP).<ref>[https://www.finlandia2017.fi/exhibition/about]. Retrieved 31 May 2017.</ref>

The exhibition included 416 different exhibits and 65 philatelic literature items in competitive classes.<ref>https://www.finlandia2017.fi/exhibition/exhibits</ref>

==Palmares==
The Grand Prix awards went to the following exhibits:<ref>https://www.finlandia2017.fi/exhibition/palmares</ref>

The Grand Prix Finlandia 2017 went to Jean Voruz (Switzerland) for ‘Geneva Postal Services 1839-1862‘.

The Grand Prix International went to Joseph Hackmey (United Kingdom) for ‘Classic Romania‘ (97 points).

The Grand Prix National went to Erkki Toivakka for ‘Finland: Finland 1856-1875‘ (96 points).

