==Background== ===Production=== The tour marked the beginning of a talent exchange working agreement between ECW and FMW which would last throughout the existence of both promotions. The theme of the tour was that ECW wrestlers would work matches on all of the shows on the tour. The tour also featured the return of FMW wrestlers, who were part of [[List of Extreme Championship Wrestling alumni|ECW roster]] at the time, [[Terry Funk]] and [[Sabu (wrestler)|Sabu]] as ECW wrestlers. Funk had been the leader of Funk Masters of Wrestling and was returning the company for the first time since beating [[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]] at Kawasaki Legend: Fall Spectacular and Sabu was returning since losing to [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]] at Summer Spectacular in 1994.<ref name="fall97"/><ref name="summer94">{{cite web|url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/fmw/miscfmw.htmlsummer94|title=FMW Summer Spectacular 1994|publisher=Pro Wrestling History|accessdate=2017-11-28}}</ref> ===Storylines=== At Kawasaki Legend: Fall Spectacular, [[Atsushi Onita]] defeated [[Kouhiro Kanemura|W*ING Kanemura]] in a [[hardcore wrestling|no rope barbed wire electrified dynamite land mine time bomb death match]] which stipulated that if Onita lost, he would [[Professional wrestling match types#Retirement match|retire]] and if Kanemura lost, then [[W*ING Alliance]] must disband.<ref name="fall97">{{cite web|url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/fmw/miscfmw.html#fall97|title=FMW Fall Spectacular 1997|publisher=Pro Wrestling History|accessdate=2017-11-28}}</ref> After the match, W*ING Alliance members Kanemura, [[Hideki Hosaka]] and [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] were concerned because no group in FMW would accept them. Onita became upset at FMW's team of [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Masato Tanaka]] and [[Koji Nakagawa]] for being rude to Kanemura, Hosaka and Hido and then he met Kanemura in his ambulance to conduct a meeting with the former W*ING members. On September 30, Onita held a press conference in which he [[Turn (professional wrestling)|turn]]ed [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villain]] for the first time in his FMW career by denouncing himself as a FMW wrestler and formed [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]] with the former W*ING Alliance and FMW's upstart [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]]. A rivalry blossomed between FMW and ZEN and the Funk Masters of Wrestling was quickly phased out after [[Mr. Gannosuke]], [[Hisakatsu Oya]] and [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]] ended it due to the group's leader [[Terry Funk]] leaving FMW and they joined ZEN.<ref name="fmwhistory">{{cite web|url=http://fmwwrestling.us/FMWHistory2.html|title=FMW History Part 2|publisher=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling|FMW Wrestling]]|accessdate=2017-11-28}}</ref> On November 20, Masato Tanaka, [[Ricky Fuji]] and Mr. Pogo #2 defeated ZEN's Atsushi Onita, Tetsuhiro Kuroda and Hido in a [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|six-man tag team match]] when Tanaka pinned Onita,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.purolove.com/misc/fmw/results/97scramble.php|title=Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling - "SCRAMBLE SURVIVOR 1997"|publisher=Puro Love|accessdate=2017-11-28|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Kitakyushu|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=246186|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-11-20}}</ref> leading to a match between the two on the first show of the Super Extreme Wrestling War tour on December 19.
At [[FMW 8th Anniversary Show|8th Anniversary Show]], Hayabusa defeated Mr. Gannosuke in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Luchas de Apuestas|mask vs. hair match]] and then attempted to reconcile with Gannosuke but Gannosuke attacked him and attempted to [[Professional wrestling attacks#Fireball|blow fire]] on him until Hayabusa's ally [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] made the save, thus forming an alliance with Hayabusa and beginning to feud with Gannosuke.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.puroresucentral.com/FMWReview-KudoRetirement.html|title=Megumi Kudo Retirement Show, 4/29/97|publisher=Puroresu Central|accessdate=2017-11-28|author=Stuart}}</ref> On June 21, Gannosuke attacked Shinzaki under a Hayabusa disguise during Shinzaki's entrance before a match at a [[Michinoku Pro Wrestling]] show.<ref name="gannosuke">{{cite web|title=Mr. Gannosuke's Bio|url=http://fmwwrestling.us/Gannosuke.html|publisher=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling|FMW Wrestling]]|accessdate=2017-11-28}}</ref> On July 19, Gannosuke, Hisakatsu Oya and The Gladiator defeated Hayabusa, Shinzaki and Koji Nakagawa in a six-man tag team match.<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Takaishi|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=243076|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-07-19}}</ref> On August 25, Gannosuke, Gladiator and [[Corporal Kirchner|Super Leather]] defeated the team of Shinzaki, Ricky Fuji and [[Ricky Morton]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Barbed Wire Massacre|barbed wire tornado deathmatch]].<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Osaka|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=243730|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-08-25}}</ref> On October 14, Gannosuke attacked Shinzaki from behind before a match between the two and then easily defeated him by making him bleed.<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Sapporo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=243791|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-10-14}}</ref> On October 19, Gannosuke, along with Hisakatsu Oya left Funk Masters of Wrestling and joined ZEN after losing the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Tag Team Championship]] to ZEN's Atsushi Onita and Yukihiro Kanemura.<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Sendai|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=244158|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-10-19}}</ref> The title would be vacated due to Onita's inactivity. On November 28, Gannosuke and Yukihiro Kanemura defeated Hayabusa and Masato Tanaka to win the vacant title.<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=246202|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-11-28}}</ref> On December 5, Gannosuke stole Shinzaki's clothes and wore them during a tag team match pitting him and Hideki Hosaka against Shinzaki and Ricky Fuji, which Gannosuke and Hosaka won.<ref>{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=246206|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-12-05}}</ref> This set up a title defense for Gannosuke and Kanemura against Hayabusa and Shinzaki on the December 19 show of the tour.
Other important changes in the FMW roster took place in December as Hisakatsu Oya quit ZEN after losing to Hayabusa on December 5 and Koji Nakagawa walked out on FMW after feeling betrayed by [[Shoichi Arai]] for not been given major opportunities which had been promised to him in the past.<ref name="fmwhistory"/> ==Events== ===Day 1=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Super Extreme Wrestling War |image=[[File:Komazawa Gymnasium & Control Tower 2009.jpg|250px]] |promotion=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling]] |date={{dts|1997|12|19}}<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19"/> |venue=[[Komazawa Gymnasium]]<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19"/> |city=[[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19"/> |attendance=5,200<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19">{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=247544|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-28|date=1997-12-19}}</ref> |liveevent=y |event= |lastevent2= |nextevent2= }} The first show of the Super Extreme Wrestling War took place on December 19, 1997 at the [[Komazawa Gymnasium]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. It was the first event in FMW history to host [[Extreme Championship Wrestling]]'s (ECW) [[List of Extreme Championship Wrestling alumni|roster]] in FMW and marked the beginning of the talent exchange between FMW and ECW wrestlers which would see wrestlers from both companies appear in interpromotional matches. In the first match, [[Fuyuki-Gun]] ([[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]], [[Jado]] and [[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]) defeated [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]] members defeated [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]], [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]] when Fuyuki performed a [[Professional wrestling attacks#Lariat|Lariat]] on Hido. [[Aja Kong]] defeated [[Shark Tsuchiya]] with a ''[[Professional wrestling attacks#Back fist|Uraken]]''. [[D-Von Dudley]] from ECW defeated [[Ricky Fuji]] with a ''[[Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers#Death Drop|Dudley Death Drop]]'' from [[Dudley Boyz]] and ZEN's [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]] defeated ECW's [[Tommy Dreamer]] with a ''[[Powerbomb#Superbomb|Super Awesome Bomb]]''. The event marked the return of the former leader of Funk Masters of Wrestling [[Terry Funk]] to FMW as an ECW wrestler. He defeated [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] and [[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray Dudley]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|three-way dance]]. [[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] retained the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Tag Team Championship]] against [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]] and [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] when Kanemura hit a diving Hayabusa in his injured ribs with his knee and then [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Roll-up|rolled him up]] to win the match. The main event of the show featured the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Heavyweight Championship|Brass Knuckles Heavyweight Champion]] and the [[FMW Independent Heavyweight Championship|Independent Heavyweight Champion]] [[Masato Tanaka]] competing against ZEN leader [[Atsushi Onita]] in a non-title match, stemming from Tanaka [[Pin (professional wrestling)|pin]]ning Onita in a match. Onita defeated Tanaka in the match.<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19"/> A dissension took place within ZEN as Onita [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Book|booked]] himself in the main event while Mr. Gannosuke and Yukihiro Kanemura grew upset as they thought that their FMW Brass Knuckles Tag Team Championship match deserved to be the main event of the show as they had become [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Over|popular]] [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]] of FMW. A clash occurred within ZEN.<ref name="fmwhistory"/> {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec19"/> |times= |match1=[[Fuyuki-Gun]] ([[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]], [[Jado]] and [[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]) defeated [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]], [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]] |stip1=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]] |time1=6:46 |match2=[[Aja Kong]] defeated [[Shark Tsuchiya]] |stip2=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |time2=13:02 |match3=[[D-Von Dudley]] defeated [[Ricky Fuji]] |stip3=Singles match |time3=8:09 |match4=[[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]] defeated [[Tommy Dreamer]] |stip4=Singles match |time4=9:52 |match5=[[Terry Funk]] defeated [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] and [[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray Dudley]] |stip5=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|Three-Way Dance]] |time5=6:32 |match6=[[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] (c) defeated [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]] and [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] |stip6=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types|Tag team match]] for the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Tag Team Championship]] |time6=17:49 |match7=[[Atsushi Onita]] defeated [[Masato Tanaka]] |stip7=Singles match |time7=20:07 }} ;Three-Way Dance eliminations {| class="wikitable" |- ! Wrestler: !! Eliminated by: !! Elimination move: !! Time: |- | The Sandman || Buh Buh Ray Dudley || ''[[Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers#Death Drop|Dudley Death Drop]]'' || 6:32 |- | Buh Buh Ray Dudley || Terry Funk || [[DDT (professional wrestling)|DDT]] || 8:18 |- !Winner: |colspan="3" |Terry Funk |- |}
===Day 2=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Super Extreme Wrestling War |image= |promotion=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling]] |date={{dts|1997|12|20}}<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20">{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=247556|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-29|date=1997-12-20}}</ref> |venue=Osaka Seaside Sports Center<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20"/> |city=[[Osaka]], [[Japan]]<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20"/> |attendance=3,600<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20"/> |liveevent=y |event= |lastevent2= |nextevent2= }} The second show of the tour took place on December 20, 1997 at the Osaka Seaside Sports Center in [[Osaka]], [[Japan]]. It drew an attendance of 3,600. In the opening match, [[Ricky Fuji]] defeated Flying Kid Ichihara with a [[Brainbuster]]. [[Kaori Nakayama]] and [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] defeated Toxic Corps (Crusher Maedomari and Miss Mongol) when Nakayama pinned Mongol with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#La magistral|la magistral]], leading to a rematch between the two teams on the next show. [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] made Mr. Pogo #2 submit to a ''[[Professional wrestling holds#Camel clutch|Gokuraku-gatame]]''. [[Fuyuki-Gun]] leader [[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]] continued his rivalry with [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]] by defeating ZEN member [[Hideki Hosaka]] as The Great Fake, with a [[Professional wrestling attacks#Lariat|running lariat]]. [[Extreme Championship Wrestling]]'s (ECW) [[Dudley Boyz]] ([[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray]] and [[D-Von Dudley|D-Von]]) fought [[Jado and Gedo]] to a no contest. ZEN's [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]], [[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] defeated ECW's [[Terry Funk]], [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] and [[Tommy Dreamer]] when Gannosuke pinned his former Funk Masters of Wrestling leader Funk with a ''[[Pin (professional wrestling)#Gannosuke Clutch|Gannosuke Clutch]]''. In the main event, [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Masato Tanaka]] and former ZEN member [[Hisakatsu Oya]] defeated ZEN's [[Atsushi Onita]], [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]] and [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] to win the [[FMW World Street Fight 6-Man Tag Team Championship]].<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20"/> {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec20"/> |times= |match1=[[Ricky Fuji]] defeated Flying Kid Ichihara |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |time1=11:48 |match2=[[Kaori Nakayama]] and [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] defeated Toxic Corps (Crusher Maedomari and Miss Mongol) |stip2=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types|Tag team match]] |time2=10:19 |match3=[[Jinsei Shinzaki]] defeated Mr. Pogo #2 via submission |stip3=Singles match |time3=8:36 |match4=[[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]] defeated [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]] |stip4=Singles match |time4=8:44 |match5=[[Dudley Boyz]] ([[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray]] and [[D-Von Dudley|D-Von]]) vs. [[Jado and Gedo]] ended in a no contest |stip5=Tag team match |time5=17:48 |match6=[[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]] ([[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]], [[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]]) defeated [[Terry Funk]], [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] and [[Tommy Dreamer]] |stip6=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]] |time6=13:48 |match7=[[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Masato Tanaka]] and [[Hisakatsu Oya]] defeated ZEN ([[Atsushi Onita]], [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]] and [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]]) (c) |stip7=Six-man tag team match for the [[FMW World Street Fight 6-Man Tag Team Championship]] |time7=17:52 }} ===Day 3=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Super Extreme Wrestling War |image=File:Aichi Prefectural Gymnasium.JPG |promotion=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling]] |date={{dts|1997|12|21}}<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21">{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=248277|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-29|date=1997-12-21}}</ref> |venue=[[Aichi Prefectural Gymnasium]]<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21"/> |city=[[Nagoya]], [[Aichi Prefecture|Aichi]], Japan<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21"/> |attendance=4,350<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21"/> |liveevent=y |event= |lastevent2= |nextevent2= }} The third show took place on December 21, 1997 at the [[Aichi Prefectural Gymnasium]] in [[Nagoya]], [[Aichi Prefecture|Aichi]], [[Japan]]. The event drew a crowd of 4,350 people. [[Hideki Hosaka]] defeated newcomer [[Mammoth Sasaki|Yoshinori Sasaki]] by making him submit to a [[Boston crab#Single-legged Boston crab|one-legged Boston crab]]. Toxic Corps (Crusher Maedomari and Miss Mongol) defeated [[Kaori Nakayama]] and [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] in a rematch from the previous show when Maedomari delivered a ''[[Chokeslam|Nodowa Otoshi]]'' to Sato. [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] gained a submission victory over Flying Kid Ichihara with a ''[[Professional wrestling holds#Camel clutch|Gokuraku-gatame]]''. [[Fuyuki-Gun]] ([[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]], [[Jado]] and [[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]) defeated the FMW team of [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Ricky Fuji]] and Mr. Pogo #2 when Fuyuki delivered a [[Professional wrestling attacks#Lariat|running lariat]] to Pogo #2. [[Mr. Gannosuke]] defeated his former tag team partner [[Hisakatsu Oya]] with a ''[[Pin (professional wrestling)#Gannosuke Clutch|Gannosuke Clutch]]''. [[Extreme Championship Wrestling]]'s (ECW) [[Terry Funk]], [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]], [[Tommy Dreamer]] and [[Dudley Boyz]] took on [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]]'s [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]], [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]], [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]], [[Atsushi Onita]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]] in an interpromotional match which Funk won by pinning Hido with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Small package|small package]]. In the main event, [[Masato Tanaka]] successfully defended the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Heavyweight Championship]] and the [[FMW Independent Heavyweight Championship]] against ZEN's [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] by performing a ''[[Professional wrestling attacks#Discus elbow smash|Roaring Elbow]]''.<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21"/> {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22">{{cite web|title=FMW @ Tokyo|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=248279|website=Wrestlingdata.com|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-29|date=1997-12-22}}</ref> |times= |match1=[[Hideki Hosaka]] defeated [[Mammoth Sasaki|Yoshinori Sasaki]] via submission |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |time1=6:21 |match2=Toxic Corps (Crusher Maedomari and Miss Mongol) defeated [[Kaori Nakayama]] and [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] |stip2=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types|Tag team match]] |time2=12:16 |match3=[[Jinsei Shinzaki]] defeated Flying Kid Ichihara via submission |stip3=Singles match |time3=8:49 |match4=[[Fuyuki-Gun]] ([[Hiromichi Fuyuki|Kodo Fuyuki]], [[Jado]] and [[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]) defeated [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Ricky Fuji]] and Mr. Pogo #2 |stip4=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Six-man tag team match]] |time4=13:42 |match5=[[Mr. Gannosuke]] and Hisakatsu Oya |stip5=Singles match |time5=16:07 |match6=[[Extreme Championship Wrestling|Team ECW]] ([[Terry Funk]], [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]], [[Tommy Dreamer]] and [[Dudley Boyz]] ([[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray]] and [[D-Von Dudley|D-Von]])) defeated [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]] ([[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]], [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]], [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]], [[Atsushi Onita]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]]) |stip6=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Ten-man tag team match]] |time6=15:57 |match7=[[Masato Tanaka]] (c) defeated [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] |stip7=Singles match for the [[FMW Brass Knuckles Heavyweight Championship]] and the [[FMW Independent Heavyweight Championship]] |time7=15:00 }}
===Day 4=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Super Extreme Wrestling War |image=[[File:Korakuen Hall 2007.jpg|250px]] |promotion=[[Frontier Martial-Arts Wrestling]] |date={{dts|1997|12|22}}<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec21"/> |venue=[[Korakuen Hall]]<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22"/> |city=Tokyo, Japan<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22"/> |attendance=2,150<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22"/> |liveevent=y |event= |lastevent2= |nextevent2= }} The final show of the Super Extreme Wrestling War tour took on December 22, 1997 at the historic [[Korakuen Hall]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. The show drew a crowd of 2,150 and marked the conclusion of [[Extreme Championship Wrestling]]'s (ECW) tour in FMW. Mr. Pogo #2 defeated [[Mammoth Sasaki|Yoshinori Sasaki]] in the opening match with a [[Professional wrestling throws#Body scissors|body scissors]]. Miss Mongol and [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] competed in a match after exchanging wins in tag team matches during the previous two shows. Mongol won the match with a [[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Senton|diving senton]]. Former [[FMW Brass Knuckles Tag Team Championship|Brass Knuckles Tag Team Champions]] [[Hisakatsu Oya]] and [[Ricky Fuji]] teamed with each other as FMW members for the first time in over a year in an unofficial reunion against [[ZEN (professional wrestling)|ZEN]]'s [[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]]. Fake pinned Fuji with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Small package|small package]]. ECW had an exhibition match in which former FMW wrestler [[Sabu (wrestler)|Sabu]] returned to the company, having competed for the last time in a loss to [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]] at Summer Spectacular in 1994. He defeated [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] with an ''[[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Diving leg drop|Arabian Facebuster]]''. [[Terry Funk]] and [[Tommy Dreamer]] defeated [[Dudley Boyz]] and ZEN members [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]] and [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|three-Way dance]].<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22"/> The main event was an important match in FMW history as it concluded the rivalry between FMW and ZEN. [[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] and [[Masato Tanaka]] took on ZEN's [[Atsushi Onita]], [[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] in a [[WarGames|WarGames barbed wire baseball bat ladder cage match]]. Gannosuke and Kanemura separated themselves from Onita and did not help him throughout the match and Hayabusa won it by performing a [[Moonsault]] from the top of the steel cage, which he had failed to execute during his match against Onita at the [[FMW 6th Anniversary Show|6th Anniversary Show]]. After the match, Gannosuke and Kanemura attacked Onita until [[Koji Nakagawa]] made the rescue for him and forced Gannosuke and Kanemura to retreat and quit ZEN, along with Hido.<ref name="fmwhistory"/> {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="purolove"/><ref name="Dec22"/> |times= |match1=Mr. Pogo #2 defeated [[Mammoth Sasaki|Yoshinori Sasaki]] |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |time1=6:28 |match2=Miss Mongol defeated [[Miwa Sato (wrestler)|Miwa Sato]] |stip2=Singles match |time2=9:33 |match3=[[Tetsuhiro Kuroda]] and [[Hideki Hosaka|The Great Fake]] defeated [[Hisakatsu Oya]] and [[Ricky Fuji]] |stip3=[[Professional wrestling tag team match types|Tag team match]] |time3=12:39 |match4=[[Sabu (wrestler)|Sabu]] defeated [[The Sandman (wrestler)|The Sandman]] |stip4=Singles match |time4=13:33 |match5=[[Terry Funk]] and [[Tommy Dreamer]] defeated [[Dudley Boyz]] ([[Bubba Ray Dudley|Buh Buh Ray]] and [[D-Von Dudley|D-Von]]) and [[Mike Awesome|The Gladiator]] and [[Hido (wrestler)|Hido]] |stip5=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|Three-Way Dance]] |time5=13:22 |match6=[[Hayabusa (wrestler)|Hayabusa]], [[Jinsei Shinzaki]] and [[Masato Tanaka]] defeated [[Atsushi Onita]], [[Mr. Gannosuke]] and [[Kouhiro Kanemura|Yukihiro Kanemura]] |stip6=[[WarGames|WarGames Barbed Wire Baseball Bat Ladder Cage match]] |time6=17:52 }} ;Three-Way Dance eliminations {| class="wikitable" |- ! Wrestler: !! Team: !! Eliminated by: !! Elimination move: !! Time: |- | Hido || The Gladiator and Hido || Buh Buh Ray Dudley || ''[[Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers#Death Drop|Dudley Death Drop]]'' || 7:59 |- | D-Von Dudley || Dudley Boyz || Terry Funk || [[DDT (professional wrestling)|DDT]] || 13:22 |- !Winners: |colspan="4" |Terry Funk and Tommy Dreamer |- |}
==Aftermath== Koji Nakagawa was added into ZEN for helping Atsushi Onita to fend off the attack of Mr. Gannosuke and Yukihiro Kanemura and ZEN ended their [[Feud (professional wrestling)|feud]] with FMW and focused on feuding with the new freelance trio of Gannosuke, Kanemura and Hido.<ref name="fmwhistory"/> On January 6, 1998, Gannosuke defeated Masato Tanaka to win the Brass Knuckles Heavyweight Championship and the Independent Heavyweight Championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=14215|title=FMW @ Tokyo|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-29|date=1998-01-06}}</ref> The following night, ZEN promoted its first show, modeled after [[Souled Out (1997)|nWo Souled Out]], which was headlined by ZEN's Onita, Nakagawa and Tetsuhiro Kuroda defeating Gannosuke, Kanemura and Hido.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=shows&show=14216|title=ZEN @ Tokyo|publisher=Wrestlingdata.com|accessdate=2017-11-29|date=1998-01-07}}</ref> After the match, Gannoskue, Kanemura and Hido attacked ZEN and Fuyuki-Gun joined them in the assault and the two groups merged to form [[Team No Respect]], which became the lead [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Stable|stable]] in FMW. Hayabusa won a tournament to become the #1 contender for the Double Championship and defeated Gannosuke for the title at the [[FMW 9th Anniversary Show|9th Anniversary Show]] while Onita lost to TNR member Kodo Fuyuki.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/fmw/1998fmwppv.html#498|title=Entertainment Wrestling Live|publisher=Pro Wrestling History|accessdate=2017-11-29}}</ref>
